#HELPS


1 MUTINY~
If you are unsatisfied with the current leadership of your clan you may mutiny
and try to take over the clan for yourself.  Depending on your clan there are
several ways to go about this.

{CHonor{x {YZealot{x {MPosse{x {GAvarice{x

State your intention to mutiny in a cnote to your clan and to immortal
declaring your intention to mutiny and 3 supporters, you or one of your
supporters must have attained a rank of at least /3.  At this point all
recruiters will be demoted and each player in the clan may vote for the
person whom they think should lead the clan.  Votes will be tallied by
an Immortal and the voting shall last for 1 week.  The loser(s) of the vote
will be ranked /0 and all of their valuables will be handed over to the  
victor.  The future of the loser in the clan is left in the hands of the
victor.

{gWarlock{x

State your intention to mutiny the leader of your robe in a cnote to your
clan and to immortal declaring your intention to mutiny and 3
supporters, you or one of your supports must have attained a rank of at
least /3.  At this point all recruiters will be demoted and each player in
the clan may vote for the person whom they think should lead the robe.
Votes will be tallied by immortal and the voting shall last for 1 week.
The loser of the vote will be ranked /0 and all of their valuables will
be handed over to the victor.  The future of the loser in the clan is left
in the hands of the victor.

{RDemise{x

State your intention to mutiny in a cnote to Demise and to immortal
declaring your intention to mutiny and 3 supporters, you or one of
your supports must have attained a rank of at least /3.  At this point
a duel will be scheduled by the immortals between the mutineer and
one of the /5's to be decided upon by the current leadership or if the
mutineer chooses to only replace one of the leaders of demise they
may declare which /5 they wish will duel. .  Should one of the parties
fail to respond to the immortals or miss the duel, they will lose by
default.   The loser(s) of the vote will be ranked /0 and all of their
valuables will be handed over to the victor.  The future of the loser
in the clan is left in the hands of the victor.

Notes about all clan mutinies:

* Attempting a mutiny is considered treasonous, should be caught
attempting to gather support for a mutiny there is high probability
that you will be outcast.

* Voting more than once or supporting with different characters of 
yours in a mutiny is considered multiplaying and will result in 
additional punishments as well as having your votes disqualified.

* Anything not covered in this help file may be decided at the
immortals digression.
~
52 OLDMUTINY~

CLAN MUTINY POLICIES:

AVARICE:

To mutiny the leader of Avarice, it is very simple. All you
need to do, is:
1.  Announce intent with the support of 1 /4.  (If you are
a /4, thats fine, support of any other member is acceptable.
2.  A vote will be held, winner takes all.  If there is a tie
then it is settled by dual.
3.  Anyone guilded within 2 weeks of the Mutiny is NOT permitted
a vote.
4.  The loser will be required to leave all EQ behind.  This is
so the leader (Whom may be holding clan funds) doesn't make
it out the door and screw the clan.  It will be up to the
winner to return any other gear.  (which would follow charter)

DEMISE:

To mutiny in Demise, you need to have five supporters who
are different characters, and you must organize the mutiny
in seret, posting the mutiny note to Demise and the immortals
once the supporters, one of which must be a /4, have been
arranged.  Otherwise, the current leader is entitled to 
outcast you at any time prior to the public posting.
In addition, you yourself must have been in Demise for
a period of two months, not necessairly consecutive months
provided you didn't join any other clan if you were a loner
at some point.  Once these requirements have been satisified,
a duel will take place in which each side may declare a champion
to fight in their place.  The winning side becomes the leader.

HONOR:

Any Mutineer must have attained the rank of /2 or above and have at
least 5 supporters, those of rank /3 only require 4 supporers, and
those of rank /4 only require 3 supporters. He must then post a note 
declaring the mutiny that includes character info, mutiny reasons and 
the names of his supporters.  If this is done, and the supporters are 
verified,1 week of voting will commence. An immortal will count the 
votes. No recruiting will take place during the week of voting.  Voting 
with alts will disqualify a person's votes.  The mutineer and /5's may 
not vote.The loser of the mutiny will be ranked /1 and will hand over all
valuables to the victor.

POSSE:

If you wish to challenge for leadership, it works as a simple
majority vote. In order to be elligible you must first gain 
support from at least 3 other posse members.Once you have 
necessary support, the election begins. Majority wins.
The parties involved (being the Leader challenged and the 
challenger) can not vote.

WARLOCK:

Majority Vote was method used in past, so as it stands that 
is the policy. An Imm would be asked to tally votes.
Mutineer would post cnote to 'Warlock Immortal' declaring mutiny
and giving name of IMM to post your vote to.
(so votes can be anonymous) 7 days from post date, vote is tallied, 
winner is /5 looser is outcast.

ZEALOT:

To mutiny in Zealot, the mutineer must be a rank /4, and have the
support of at least 5 other members who have been ranked above /0
and who have been in the clan for at least one month's time.
The Anointed then has the choice to either settle the dispute
via a duel, or a clan vote.
If a duel is called for, an IMM will supervise on a preset date which
will be at least one week after the mutiny was called. The duel will
be to the death, with no charmies. Cheaters will lose automatically.
If the Anointed does not wish to duel, he or she may call for a
clan vote, which shall last for a period of one week. During that
time, all /4s shall be reduced to /0 until the vote is decided, or
one of the contesting parties withdraws.

The loser of either contest will be at the winner's discretion.

~


-1 hlab~

The Infamous Prefresh

Q. What is it?
A. The prefresh is short for "player refresh".  It is a process by which all
current player files (the file that contains the data about your character in
fixed storage) and updated to the current MHS game code.

Q. How often will we do this?
A. If we do it right and make changes correectly, once and once only.

Q. How will I know when I am being prefreshed?
A. You will be given a 10-day advanced warning before we do it.  We will also
run a handful of tests that players can volunteer to put themselves through
to make sure there are no bugs.

Q. What will happen to my character when I prefresh?
A. When the day arrives you will log in and the game will detect that your
character is not marked as being prefreshed already.  You'll be put into a
sort of secondary creation mode.  You will be told that you need to prefresh
and an image of your player file will be backed up to a special directory just
in case something goes wrong.  The game will store in a special data structure
a copy of your important data, and then you'll have to select which method of
prefresh you want to use.  You'll be guided through the process from there.

Q. What are my options?
A. Option #1 is the Standard Prefresh.  What happens is that your character
is set to level 1 and you go to the alignment selection screen.  You pick your
alignment, and then you to the stat customization screen.  Once that is done,
you are put back into the game at level 1, and your skills will all default
back to their original values.  When you type "score", you'll see that you
have an item called "debit levels".  You may use these at any time to level.


~

