-1 NOTE NOTES SPOOL BUG CHANGE NEWS INOTE ONOTE CNOTE GNOTE IDEA QNOTE~
The notes on MHS replace the bulletin boards and mail systems found on many
other sleds.  There are several types of notes including In-Character notes 
(inotes), Out-of-Character Notes(onotes), Bug Notes (bug), Quest Notes (qnotes) 
and God Notes (gnote). 
The following options are usable(in this case, an inote is used as an example, for other types of notes, simply replace inote with the appropriate type of note):

reading notes:
inote list	: show all inotes (unread notes are marked with an N)
inote read	: either by number, or read next to read unread inotes
inote remove	: removes an inote that you wrote or are the target of
inote catchup	: markes all inotes as read
spool           : Catches up all notes of all types
unread          : Lists notes that have not been read by this character

writing new notes:
inote to	: sets the to line (name, clanname, 'clans', immortal, or all)
inote subject	: sets the subject for a new inote
inote +		: adds a line to a new inote (i.e. inote + hi guys!)
inote -		: remove a line from an inote in progress
inote clear	: erase an inote in progress
note show	: shows the inote you are working on
inote post	: posts a new inote. This MUST be done to post an inote.

When you log in, you will be informed if there are unread notes waiting. Type
note read to scroll through them one at a time.

Four other note directories exist, these are ideas, news, changes, and 
penalties (gods only).  They are used the exact same way, for example
idea read 5 will read idea #5.  Posting to the news and changes boards is
restricted. The 'unread' command can be used to show your unread notes on
all the note spools.

~
